# 🏥 Hospital Information Management System (HIMS)

A comprehensive MySQL-based Hospital Information Management System to streamline hospital operations including patient handling, doctor scheduling, appointment booking, billing, and medical records management.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on developing a structured database system to automate and manage day-to-day hospital activities. It provides an efficient backend for hospitals to manage patients, doctors, appointments, prescriptions, billing, and pharmacy stocks.

---

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

- **Database:** MySQL  
- **Interface:** MySQL Workbench  
- **Design Tools:** dbdiagram.io (for ER Diagram)  

---

## 🎯 Key Features

- Patient registration and management  
- Doctor and department allocation  
- Appointment scheduling and status tracking  
- Medical records with prescriptions  
- Pharmacy stock tracking and linking with prescriptions  
- Automated billing and payment status  
- Role-based structure with scalable design

---

## 📊 ER Diagram

![ER Diagram](./hims_er_diagram.png)  
*(Visual representation of relationships among tables like Patients, Doctors, Appointments, Billing, etc.)*

---

## 📄 Report Summary

The Hospital Information Management System (HIMS) offers a relational database structure to manage critical data related to hospital operations. With normalized tables and foreign key constraints, the system ensures data integrity, prevents redundancy, and supports efficient querying.

This database solution can serve as a foundation for a full-fledged web or desktop hospital management application, integrating authentication, admin panels, and report generation in the future.

---

## ✅ Conclusion

The HIMS database project successfully demonstrates how structured relational models can handle complex real-world scenarios. It improves hospital service delivery by digitizing and linking all key records, making the process faster, more reliable, and easier to scale.

---

